Anniversary of Korea's Liberation Celebrated 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 24 (KCNA) -- A meeting was held at the Karachi Art Center of Pakistan, a meeting and a film show on the Koba Farm of Guinea and a friendship meeting and a joint performance in Sihanouk of Cambodia on the occasion of the 60th anniversary of the liberation of Korea.
 A Korean film "Rivers and Mountains of the Country Changing More Beautifully under the Leadership of the Great General" was screened at the film show. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Taji Haider, press secretary of the Pakistan People's Party and former senator of Pakistan, in a speech at the meeting, highly praised the undying feats of President Kim Il Sung who embarked upon the road of revolution in his early years, liberated the country, successfully realized the cause of building the Party, the state and the army and turned the DPRK into a powerful socialist industrial country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The secretary general of the People's Democratic Party of Pakistan said that Kim Il Sung is the great man and the great master of politics well-known to the world. The DPRK will win victory after victory and be surely reunified as it is led by Kim Jong Il, he stressed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The governor of Koba of Guinea noted at the meeting that Kim Il Sung  indicated the orientation and ways for achieving national liberation and building a new state in different African countries and gave moral and material assistance to them and, in particular, actively encouraged Guinea to build a new society. The Guinean people are looking up to the DPRK led by Kim Jong Il as the beacon of hope, he noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The secretary general of the Cambodian Wrestling Federation said at the friendship meeting that Kim Il Sung paid special attention to the friendship between Cambodia and the DPRK and gave moral and material assistance to Cambodia. And he expressed thanks to Kim Jong Il and the DPRK government for paying deep attention to the development of the friendly relations between the two countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, a national meeting, a photo and handicraft exhibition and a film show took place in Peru to celebrate the 60th anniversary of Korea's liberation.
 A Korean film "They Were Always Together on the Road to Bring about the People's Well-being" was screened at the film show. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Congratulatory messages to Kim Jong Il were adopted at the meetings in Pakistan and Peru.

Settlement of Japan's Past Crimes Urged 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 24 (KCNA) -- We will never forget the monstrous massacres of Koreans committed by the Japanese imperialists, including the case of Ukishima-maru sunk down by explosion but settle accounts with Japan for its past crimes at any cost through generations.
 The Association of Korean Victims of Forcible Drafting and Their Bereaved Families declared this in a statement Tuesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As well known, on August 24, 1945, the Japanese imperialists deliberately exploded Ukishima-maru, a transport ship of the imperial Japanese navy, in the sea off Maizuru Port in Kyoto Prefecture, leaving thousands of innocent Koreans, who were aboard for returning home with a joy at the liberation of the country, drowned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan kidnapped and took away millions of Koreans and forced toilsome labor upon them, and even drowned thousands of them at once in retaliation of its defeat in the war. Nevertheless, it has persistently evaded its responsibility for the crimes and, on the contrary, is now hell-bent on the anti-DPRK moves while peddling the issue of the remains of "abducted Japanese" which had been already settled. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The association, on behalf of all the Korean victims of forcible drafting and their bereaved families, bitterly denounces such shameless behavior of the Japanese authorities, branding it as the most despicable inhumane crime.
 The Japanese authorities should have a clear understanding of the will of the Korean nation and make a thoroughgoing probe into the truth about all the inhuman crimes committed by Japan against the Korean people in the past. They should promptly take a practical step to make an honest apology and compensation to the victims and their bereaved families.

Symposium of Historians Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 24 (KCNA) -- A symposium of historians was held by the Academy of Social Sciences Tuesday, 60 years since Ukishima-maru was blown up by the Japanese imperialists.
 Present there were Thae Hyong Chol, president of the Academy of Social Sciences, officials concerned and teachers and researchers in the field of social science and of universities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers cited concrete historical facts to prove that the case was an inhuman and national chauvinistic massacre of Koreans committed by the Japanese imperialists. They disclosed what monstrous crimes were committed by the Japanese imperialists against those aboard the ship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese authorities are falsifying truth about the incident which claimed thousands of civilian casualties, while dastardly working to keep the incident buried into oblivion at any cost, understating the number of the victims, the speakers said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Worse still, Japan views the incident from the political view-point of negating its past crimes. Even the legal circle of Japan tends to back the stand of its government. The reality indicates that a proper settlement of the incident presents itself as one of the political and legal issues related to protecting and exercising the dignity and sovereignty of the Korean nation. 
 The speakers strongly charged that the blowing up of the ship was a grave international criminal act of blatantly challenging justice and moral sense of the international community and gravely violating international law as it was perpetrated by the Japanese military authorities in a premeditated and deliberate manner with the approval of the Japanese government.
 The army and the people of the DPRK will carry on their struggle, true to the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il, till Japan, the sworn enemy, fully apologizes and compensates for all its past crimes.

45th Anniv. of Kim Jong Il's Start of Songun Revolutionary Leadership
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 24 (KCNA) -- A meeting of the Ministry of the People's Armed Forces took place at the April 25 House of Culture Wednesday to celebrate the 45th anniversary of Supreme Commander Kim Jong Il's start of Songun revolutionary leadership.
 On Aug. 25, Juche 49 (1960) he visited the Guard Seoul Ryu Kyong Su 105 tank division and left the first giant footprint of the Songun revolutionary leadership, thus performing noteworthy exploits in the development of the revolutionary armed forces and the accomplishment of the revolutionary cause of Juche. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Addressing the meeting, Kim Yong Chun, chief of the KPA General Staff, said this. He continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il had the Party's e leadership system   established within the People's Army in the 1960s, set forth the programme of modeling the whole army on the Juche idea and the slogan of loyalty "Let's devote a life to the fight for the great leader!" before the army in the 1970s and thus provided a new landmark of building the Party's army of Juche type. In the 1980s, too, he wisely led the drive for further strengthening and developing the People's Army into a revolutionary army unfailingly loyal to the Party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il developed in depth the Songun politics and Songun leadership to meet the requirements of the developing revolution and trained the army to be vanguard ranks of devotedly demanding the leader, a strong revolutionary army of Mt. Paektu in the 1990s. He is wisely leading the army holding higher the banner of Songun in the new century so that the army may form an integral whole with the supreme commander and fulfill its noble mission in the first line of the Songun revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter said that all the officials and servicemen should prepare themselves as the first-line fighters, first-line human bombs in defence of the headquarters of the revolution headed by Kim Jong Il and strengthen the ideological might of arms. He underscored the need for serviceman to put spurs to strengthening the combat power of the army and completing preparations for fighting with firm anti-imperialist and working class consciousness and fighting spirit and mercilessly wipe out the enemies and accomplish the historic cause of national reunification if the enemies invade even an inch of sky, land and sea of the sacred country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meeting was attended by KPA Vice Marshals Jo Myong Rok, director of the KPA General Political Department, Kim Yong Chun, chief of the KPA General Staff, and Kim Il Chol, minister of the People's Armed Forces.

New Plastic Material Developed in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 24 (KCNA) -- The Hamhung Branch Academy under the Academy of Sciences of the Democratic People�fs Republic of Korea has succeeded in developing a new kind of synthetic plastic material with advanced technology.
 Its mechanical intensity is 120-130Mpa. The material stands against the temperature of 140-150 degrees centigrade and 40 bars. It can replace iron or stainless steel of machines working in condition of excessive erosion, abrasion and high pressure. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its resistance to acid is over 10 times those of iron and stainless steel and its quality remains unchanged even after more than 50 years. 
 The weight of the machines made of this material is light to sharply reduce motor load and bearing abrasion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The pipeline made of the material for transport of concentrated ore is abraded only 0.1 millimeters annually compared with 1.5 mm-abrasion of the stainless steel one. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Years of test shows that the valves of this material are no less than the stainless steel ones. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Scientists of the branch academy have established a technical process so as to easily make the material with raw materials of the country anywhere and thus opened a prospect for widely using this new material in all sectors of the national economy.

Physical Culture and Sports Popularized in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 24 (KCNA) -- Physical culture and sports activities have become brisk among people in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 In the July-August months of aquatic sports, people including youth and students have taken part in colorful water sports activities at swimming pools on Panwol Islet and at Changgwang Health Complex, the wading pool in Mangyongdae in Pyongyang and bathing resorts in Songdowon, Majon and other scenic spots. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Many sports events have been held in August in which the 60th anniversary of Korean liberation fell. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There were sports games and amusements of women in Pyongyang at Mangyongdae Fun Fair on August 11. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Participating in them were more than 3,000 players selected from Central, Moranbong and other districts and counties of the capital.
 The women players, divided into "Haebang (Liberation) Team" and "Thongil (Reunification) Team", fully demonstrated their sports technique at 12 events.
 On August 15, there were a performance of the mass gymnastic display "Under the Banner of Songun" given by 10,000 schoolchildren in Yonan County, South Hwanghae Province and sports games and amusements held by over 2,500 officials of provincial-level institutions in Wonsan City, Kangwon Province.
 Some days ago residents of neighborhood units of Tongsin-dong No.3 in Tongdaewon District, Pyongyang, met in football, volleyball and yut games, drawing public attention. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Employees of the industrial establishments throughout the country take morning running and exercises during recesses every day and observe Day of Sports every month. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the performers of the grand mass gymnastic and artistic performance "Arirang" are strikingly demonstrating the physical strength and sports technique they have cultivated through their everyday physical culture activities.

Talks Held between Yang Hyong Sop and Zambian Vice-President
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 24 (KCNA) -- Talks between Yang Hyong Sop, vice-president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, and Lupando Mwape, vice-president of the Republic of Zambia, took place at the Mansudae Assembly Hall Wednesday.
 At the talks two sides exchanged views on the issue of positively boosting the friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries in various fields and a series of issues of bilateral interest. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The talks proceeded in a friendly atmosphere. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there from the DPRK side were Kim Hyong Jun, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs, Ri Myong San, vice-minister of Foreign Trade, Kim Yong Suk, vice-minister of Agriculture, and others and from the Zambian side Davison Mulela, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs, Mbita Chitala, vice-minister of Finance and National Planning, James Kaiuka, vice-minister of Agriculture and Cooperation, Peter Harry Filamba, vice-minister of Tourism, Environment and National Resources, David Clifford Saviye, Zambian ambassador e.p. to the DPRK, and other members of the delegation.

Spokesman for DPRK FM. Denounces Ulji Focus Lens-05 Joint Military Exercises
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 24 (KCNA) -- We have shown utmost magnanimity and flexibility as regards the issue of denuclearizing the Korean Peninsula but will never do such a thing as yielding to anyone's pressure and abandoning our sovereign right.
 A spokesman for the Foreign Ministry of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea stated this in an answer given to a question put by KCNA Wednesday in connection with the Ulji Focus Lens-05 joint military exercises launched by the United States in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recalling that the U.S.-south Korea "Combined Forces Command" launched the joint military exercises on August 22 despite the repeated warnings of the DPRK, the spokesman said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We cannot but take a serious view of such perfidious act of the U.S. as staging the provocative war maneuvers targeted against the dialogue partner after expressing its will not to invade the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. undisguised military hostility towards the DPRK only compels it to explicitly interpret the U.S. expression of its will for a peaceful solution to the nuclear issue as no more than hypocrisy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Dialogue and confrontation can never go together. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the U.S. persistently incites confrontation and pursues dialogue as a smokescreen to cover up it, this will also compel the DPRK to change its stand toward dialogue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The fact that the U.S. launched the above-said military exercises on the eve of the resumption of the six-party talks that had gone into temporary recess cannot be construed otherwise than an attempt to force the DPRK to accept its unjust demand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is sadly mistaken if it calculates it can get any concession from the DPRK by military pressure or high-handed practice. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the facts go to prove what just step the DPRK has taken to bolster all the deterrent forces under the banner of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK is closely following all the developments.
